<br>
He recovered though and managed to save some face, by clearing his throat, nodding lightly, as though he'd known that the sacrifice would not take place in the village all along.  He smiled at her, &quot;Forgive me if I do not participate in the ceremony later?&quot;  His eyes focused on her for a moment, and his mind raced with thoughts, 'By the gods, she has the most incredible eyes.'  He swallowed hard, moved towards her slightly.  &quot;Vasillissa, if you are not otherwise occupied in the morn, perhaps you'd accompany me on my morning walk and then breakfast?&quot;  Of course he was asking for more time alone with her, what man in their right mind wouldn't?  Course then again, what man in their right mind would? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=alexiares>Alexiares</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#993300>(5/15/03 9:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=472.topic&index=69>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/queenhippolyte/images/alexiares.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> A little dancing</span><hr size=1> Alexi had drank a little wine.  Quietly watching everyone from the side of the pavilion.  She still didn't know very many of those there.  She saw Theseus talking to someone who looked very important.  And then Solari near them.  Thank the Goddess for Solari and the others, Alexiares reminded herself.  For here she was, free.<br>
<br>
The sound of music at one end of the pavilion caught Alexiares's ears.  A grin graced her face, as quickly her feet began to move her over towards the sound.  This was something that she knew and was sure of.  Like the beat of her heart, music was life to Alexiares.  Her palms seem to lift up magically, her wrists twisting them upwards.  Her barefeet began to move across the floor of the pavilion in a light dance.  The little silver bells on her ankles and wrists light sounding as her hips began to sway with her feet's movement.  Her palms upstretched to the Gods, Alexi danced gazing up in praise.  Spinning ever so slightly from time to time, the dancer had a calm relaxed smile. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=archeressofdaggerpoint>Archeress of Daggerpoint</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 57<br> <font color=#993300>(5/16/03 1:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=472.topic&index=70>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Leaving?</span><hr size=1> Tala watched the others quietly for a long time, leaning back against the wall in silent thought. Awhile back she had gone to Sarmatia and had been confronted by the High Priestess of Avalon there. Offered a chance as a priestess, Tala had lept at the opportunity. Now it was only a matter of telling the Vasilissas she'd be going...she didn't want to be concidered a deserter after all. She snapped out of her thoughts and looked around, then took a breath and moved away from the wall, through the crowd and over to Vasilissa Delerium. She saluted her, her gaze flicking over to the man next to her, then back. &quot;Vasilissa...please excuse m'interuption. May I speak wif you m'Queen?&quot; As much as she tried to be formal, her heavy accent just made it sound funny. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=theseusofthemiscrya>Theseus of Themiscrya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 46<br> <font color=#993300>(5/16/03 4:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=472.topic&index=71>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Interruption Acknowledged</span><hr size=1> Theseus knew well that when an amazon interrupts a conversation with the queen it is best that he allow the interruption without further incident.  He nodded to the amazon, smiled at her slightly, then glanced to Delerium.  &quot;I'll leave you two girls to talk.&quot;  <br>
<br>
He left the area as dignified and gracefully as possible.  His eyes moved over the form of Alexiares as she danced.  He quickly ordered more to drink given that her movements were having a fully anticipated reaction out of him.  He swallowed hard and leaned against a post to watch her dance.  He was lost watching her fluid movements. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hippolyte>Hippolyte</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Platinum Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 960<br> <font color=#993300>(5/16/03 4:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=472.topic&index=72>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.themiscrya.i-p.com/Hippwknife1ezboard.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Interruption Acknowledged</span><hr size=1> Hippolyte had caught Theseus leaving his attentions from De'Lerium.  Walking around the edge of the Pavilion, she soon was standing behind her son.  As he leaned against the post, Hippolyte let her eyes follow his without him knowing.  A smirk danced on her lips, as she saw her son watching the beautiful Alexiares dance.  For a moment, even Hippolyte watched ...lost in the dance of the dancer priestess.  She was beautiful.  As was De'L....Themiscrya held many beautiful women.  And her son was a young man.<br>
<br>
The queen thought for a bit, she didn't know how to take what was happening.  There was always a risk with the amazon women...that they might find a male they desired to live their lives out with.  And then..they would leave the tribe.  Normally, Hippolyte would do all she could to hinder such a match.  But, this was her son...<br>
<br>
Hippolyte's head began to tilt to the side as it did, when she gazed upon something deep in thought. Then taking herself out of the thoughts, she spoke to her son from behind, &quot;Many beautiful women in Themiscrya...are there not, son?&quot;  It was more of a statement..then a question.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=theseusofthemiscrya>Theseus of Themiscrya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 48<br> <font color=#993300>(5/16/03 8:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=472.topic&index=73>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The Wonders of the Amazon World</span><hr size=1> The queen's son smiled as he moved his eyes from the dancing priestess.  He turned them to his mother.  &quot;Yes, there are.&quot;  His own eyes sought out Delerium talking with the other amazon.  &quot;Some more beautiful than I remember them being.&quot;  He continued to gaze at Delerium for a few moments.  Theseus took a long drink of his drink and then cleared his throat, trying to cover up his own nervousness.  &quot;I guess she's not come back here yet?&quot;  His eyes looked a little sad at the mention of his other mother.  &quot;Have you word from her? Is she alright?&quot;  He kept his voice low, but it was obvious that he missed both of his mothers.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hippolyte>Hippolyte</A></span><br> <span class=